WEBVTT

00:59.711 --> 01:01.191
- Yo, you good, bro?

01:01.235 --> 01:02.671
Drew, you okay man?

01:02.714 --> 01:03.498
- Yeah.

01:03.541 --> 01:04.847
- Are you sure, man?

01:04.890 --> 01:05.935
I can pull over
if you need me to.

01:07.110 --> 01:08.024
- No, I'm good, bro.

01:09.591 --> 01:10.287
Crazy dream.

01:13.943 --> 01:15.292
It looks so different out here.

01:16.554 --> 01:18.730
- It's not that
different at all, man.

01:18.774 --> 01:21.037
I mean, we got some new
houses and new schools,

01:21.081 --> 01:23.170
but that's pretty much it, bro.

01:25.911 --> 01:27.391
It's good to have you back home,

01:28.349 --> 01:29.437
and in one piece, man.

01:31.091 --> 01:33.832
Drew, we was worried about
you for a few days man.

01:35.791 --> 01:37.140
- I was worried for a few days.

01:38.794 --> 01:40.448
It's only by the grace of
God that I'm still here.

01:40.491 --> 01:42.580
- Yo, it got that
crazy out there?

01:46.410 --> 01:47.846
- Yeah, it got pretty crazy.

01:50.066 --> 01:51.981
- How come you never
said anything, man?

01:53.417 --> 01:55.637
- I didn't want pops
to stress too much.

01:55.680 --> 01:56.942
So I kept some of it to myself.

01:59.206 --> 02:00.468
We could talk about this later.

02:01.469 --> 02:02.600
Man, I'm home.

02:02.644 --> 02:04.167
- Yeah, you home.

02:04.211 --> 02:06.648
And we definitely gonna finish
this conversation later.

02:06.691 --> 02:08.650
I ain't letting you off
the hook that easy, bro.

02:08.693 --> 02:10.130
-  All right.

02:10.173 --> 02:10.826
- Anyway, man.

02:12.349 --> 02:15.483
Pops made a special
dinner for you.

02:17.180 --> 02:17.789
Yeah, buddy.

02:20.488 --> 02:22.011
So let's go be a family.

02:23.360 --> 02:26.407
-  Let's go be a family.

02:29.061 --> 02:30.193
-  Surprise!

02:36.112 --> 02:37.200
- Welcome home, son.

02:44.947 --> 02:47.123
- Are we done hugging
yet, 'cause I'm hungry!

02:50.257 --> 02:53.042
- All right, come on, let's eat.

03:03.226 --> 03:05.054
- Thank you, thank all of you.

03:06.011 --> 03:07.361
I cannot tell you how much

03:07.404 --> 03:08.971
I really appreciate all of this.

03:11.278 --> 03:13.758
I haven't seen a meal like
this in almost a year.

03:13.802 --> 03:16.935
- Baby boy, it is my pleasure.

03:16.979 --> 03:19.895
I'm just glad to see
you back home again.

03:19.938 --> 03:21.505
- Yeah, it's good to
have you back, Drew.

03:21.549 --> 03:22.376
- We really missed you.

03:22.419 --> 03:23.812
- I missed you all too.

03:25.117 --> 03:26.510
- I hope you're
here for a while.

03:26.554 --> 03:29.252
- You don't have to
leave at 08, do you?

03:29.296 --> 03:30.340
- No, actually, I don't
have to leave again.

03:30.384 --> 03:32.734
I got what they call
an Honorable Discharge.

03:32.777 --> 03:34.736
- What does Honorable
Discharge mean?

03:34.779 --> 03:37.652
- Well, in this case it
means I did a great job,

03:37.695 --> 03:39.784
but unfortunately, I got hurt,

03:39.828 --> 03:41.395
so I get to come home early.

03:41.438 --> 03:43.223
- How did you get hurt?

03:43.266 --> 03:46.138
- See, this is why we
need a kid's table.

03:48.010 --> 03:49.707
Let the boy breathe
before we get into

03:49.751 --> 03:50.665
all this heavy stuff.

03:51.709 --> 03:53.233
- I'm sorry, Drew.

03:53.276 --> 03:55.409
- No, it's okay, Keke.

03:55.452 --> 03:57.889
So, what you been up to?

03:57.933 --> 03:59.064
What did I miss?

03:59.108 --> 04:00.283
- You missed everything.

04:00.327 --> 04:02.285
I joined the Girl
Scouts a few months ago,

04:02.329 --> 04:03.721
and already I've
sold more cookies

04:03.765 --> 04:05.854
than any other girl in
the entire district.

04:05.897 --> 04:07.812
- Yeah, that's because
you got mom to harass

04:07.856 --> 04:09.727
all of her coworkers
to buy those cookies.

04:09.771 --> 04:11.512
Mom did all the work.

04:11.555 --> 04:12.687
- I still helped.

04:12.730 --> 04:14.297
- You ate more
cookies than you sold.

04:15.385 --> 04:17.213
-  Anyway,
haters gonna hate.

04:18.562 --> 04:20.216
- So, Jordan, what
you been up to?

04:20.260 --> 04:22.262
- I joined the dance
team at school.

04:22.305 --> 04:23.785
-  You
said dance team,

04:23.828 --> 04:25.090
you joined a dance team?

04:25.134 --> 04:26.440
I didn't even know
you had rhythm.

04:26.483 --> 04:27.702
- Exactly!

04:27.745 --> 04:29.225
- I've been taking
dance classes.

04:29.269 --> 04:32.315
- Yeah, we went to one
of his talent shows,

04:32.359 --> 04:34.012
the boy's pretty good.

04:34.056 --> 04:36.363
Go ahead, show your cousin
some of those moves.

04:36.406 --> 04:37.277
- Right now?

04:37.320 --> 04:38.495
- Right now.

04:38.539 --> 04:40.236
If you don't dance,
you don't eat.

04:41.585 --> 04:42.804
- Do that one where
you pump your fist

04:42.847 --> 04:44.240
in the air, like this.

04:44.284 --> 04:45.285
I like that one.

04:49.245 --> 04:51.073
- No, no, no, that's not it.

04:51.116 --> 04:52.901
Do the whole thing.

04:52.944 --> 04:54.294
- Go ahead, Usher.

04:54.337 --> 04:55.251
Do the whole thing.

04:55.295 --> 04:57.253
- But I don't have any music.

04:57.297 --> 04:58.210
- Theo.

04:58.254 --> 04:59.734
- Yes sir?
- Give the boy a beat.

04:59.777 --> 05:00.691
Something funky.

05:00.735 --> 05:01.649
- Aight, coming right up.

05:03.390 --> 05:04.216
-  Oh, they
put you on the spot.

05:04.260 --> 05:06.218
- Oh, I gotta see this.

05:06.262 --> 05:07.002
Come on.

05:07.045 --> 05:08.612
Jordan, Jordan, Jordan!

05:10.179 --> 05:11.963
- Okay, okay.

05:12.007 --> 05:13.051
Feast your eyes.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.707
-  Jordan, Jordan, Jordan!

05:21.625 --> 05:22.974
- There you go!

05:23.018 --> 05:24.846
That's how you do it, man.

05:24.889 --> 05:26.108
That's how you do it.

05:26.151 --> 05:28.284
Hey now, can you
do the Running Man?

05:31.418 --> 05:34.899
-  Go Jordan,
go Jordan, go Jordan!

05:34.943 --> 05:36.161
- Aw.

05:36.205 --> 05:39.164
Okay, dinner's ready, everyone.

05:39.208 --> 05:40.818
- Can I help you
with that, Auntie?

05:40.862 --> 05:42.429
- Can you go grab
the rest of the food

05:42.472 --> 05:43.908
out of the kitchen then?

05:43.952 --> 05:44.909
Thank you.

05:44.953 --> 05:46.302
- As usually, Sis.

05:46.346 --> 05:48.043
Everything looks delicious.

05:48.086 --> 05:49.218
-  Thank you.

05:49.261 --> 05:50.567
- Everyone, grab a hand.

05:56.181 --> 05:59.446
Father God, creator of
the heavens and Earth,

05:59.489 --> 06:02.710
first and foremost,
thank you for

06:02.753 --> 06:06.540
bringing my son home
safe and in one piece.

06:06.583 --> 06:09.804
And thank you for
his brothers in arms

06:09.847 --> 06:14.548
who had his back in some
very dangerous places.

06:14.591 --> 06:17.855
Thank you for the
brave men and women

06:17.899 --> 06:21.642
who continue to
protect our country.

06:21.685 --> 06:25.341
Thank you for family and friends

06:25.385 --> 06:28.779
who are always there when
you need them the most.

06:28.823 --> 06:31.782
And thank you for
this wonderful food

06:31.826 --> 06:36.439
that my sister was so
gracious in preparing.

06:36.483 --> 06:39.268
Bless it so that it
does our bodies good.

06:39.311 --> 06:40.051
Amen.

06:40.095 --> 06:41.662
-  Amen!

06:41.705 --> 06:43.794
- All right, what
are we waiting for?

06:43.838 --> 06:44.839
Dig in.

07:24.226 --> 07:26.315
- Come on man,
you can't stop me.

07:26.358 --> 07:27.011
Oh, oh.

07:29.231 --> 07:30.362
Oh, oh, oh!

07:37.500 --> 07:39.328
- Nice try, Officer.

07:39.371 --> 07:40.416
You trying to go again?

07:40.460 --> 07:41.548
-  No, thanks.

07:41.591 --> 07:43.027
I've schooled you enough
for today, I think.

07:43.071 --> 07:44.638
- More like been schooled
enough for today.

07:48.511 --> 07:50.252
- Let me give you a hand.

07:50.295 --> 07:51.035
You all right?

07:51.079 --> 07:51.906
- Yeah, perfect.

07:51.949 --> 07:53.081
Never better.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.648
Stay in school, say no to drugs.

07:55.866 --> 07:57.389
- Don't do drugs?

07:57.433 --> 07:58.478
Very original.

08:06.094 --> 08:08.009
- How are we supposed to look
like cool police officers

08:08.052 --> 08:10.359
if you're out here falling
down all over the place?

08:10.402 --> 08:12.622
- I'm just trying to
interact with the community.

08:12.666 --> 08:14.668
- Looks like you're trying to
interact with the pavement.

08:14.711 --> 08:15.799
- Jokes.

08:15.843 --> 08:17.540
Again with the jokes.

08:17.584 --> 08:19.499
You know, I've been taken
a few spills out there,

08:19.542 --> 08:20.412
but I'm getting to
know as many people

08:20.456 --> 08:22.153
in this neighborhood as I can.

08:22.197 --> 08:23.111
- I get it.

08:23.154 --> 08:24.460
I get what you're trying to do,

08:24.504 --> 08:26.201
but you don't want to
look like you're trying.

08:26.244 --> 08:27.637
- Does it look like
I'm trying too hard?

08:27.681 --> 08:28.943
- A little bit.

08:28.986 --> 08:30.727
However, it's good to try hard.

08:30.771 --> 08:33.774
But you don't want to look
like you're trying too hard.

08:33.817 --> 08:35.427
- I'm confused.

08:35.471 --> 08:36.777
- That's all right, kid.

08:36.820 --> 08:39.301
You're still new on the
job, you'll pick it up.

08:39.344 --> 08:39.997
Here you go.

08:40.998 --> 08:41.956
Have a coffee.

08:53.620 --> 08:54.359
- Hey!

08:55.752 --> 08:57.362
- How are you, sir?

08:57.406 --> 08:58.146
Good to see you.

08:58.189 --> 08:58.842
- Oh!

08:59.930 --> 09:01.541
Look who the cat dragged in!

09:01.584 --> 09:03.194
- Long time no see.

09:03.238 --> 09:05.545
- Mitchell, welcome home.

09:05.588 --> 09:07.677
- Feels good to be back
on American soil I'll bet.

09:07.721 --> 09:09.200
- Yes, it does.

09:09.244 --> 09:10.375
- Hey, welcome home kid.

09:11.681 --> 09:12.639
- Thank you, sir.

09:12.682 --> 09:14.466
- Gentlemen, enjoy.

09:15.511 --> 09:16.817
- Thank you.

09:16.860 --> 09:18.166
Hey, now that you're back,

09:18.209 --> 09:20.864
and you have all the
time in the world,

09:20.908 --> 09:22.344
what are you gonna
do with yourself?

09:22.387 --> 09:23.867
- I have a couple things
that I'm working on.

09:23.911 --> 09:25.390
And I'm looking
forward to getting back

09:25.434 --> 09:26.653
to the after school program,

09:26.696 --> 09:28.306
and another little
something me and the guys

09:28.350 --> 09:29.481
have been working on.

09:29.525 --> 09:30.526
- And the girl.

09:30.570 --> 09:31.701
I helped too.

09:33.224 --> 09:36.880
- What's this little
something ya'll talking about?

09:36.924 --> 09:38.665
- Are we allowed
to talk about it?

09:38.708 --> 09:40.014
I haven't really
told anybody yet.

09:40.057 --> 09:41.406
- No time like the present, bro.

09:42.451 --> 09:44.061
- Drew?

09:44.105 --> 09:46.934
- Well, we're looking to expand
the after school program.

09:46.977 --> 09:48.239
We've been trying to get a grant

09:48.283 --> 09:49.763
so we can open up
our own facility

09:49.806 --> 09:51.547
and get some new equipment.

09:51.591 --> 09:54.550
- When did you find
time to chase grants?

09:54.594 --> 09:55.769
- Well, when we weren't
out chasing bad guys,

09:55.812 --> 09:57.640
I had some down time.

09:57.684 --> 09:59.468
But Tracy and Christopher,

09:59.511 --> 10:01.470
they've been spearheading
the whole thing.

10:03.211 --> 10:04.429
- Are you planning on keeping it

10:04.473 --> 10:05.561
in this neighborhood?

10:05.605 --> 10:06.867
- Oh yeah, absolutely.

10:06.910 --> 10:08.564
We want to focus
all of our efforts

10:08.608 --> 10:10.044
right here in this area

10:10.087 --> 10:11.436
because we believe if you
can change the community,

10:11.480 --> 10:12.612
you can change the city.

10:13.656 --> 10:14.657
- That's brilliant!

10:16.006 --> 10:18.705
How am I just now
hearing about this?

10:18.748 --> 10:19.880
- Pops, it's still kind of new,

10:19.923 --> 10:22.752
and we're working out
the kinks, but you know,

10:22.796 --> 10:24.798
this is the direction
that we're heading in.

10:24.841 --> 10:25.581
- That's good, man.

10:25.625 --> 10:27.278
I'm happy for you.

10:27.322 --> 10:29.846
It's good to come home with
a purpose already laid out.

10:29.890 --> 10:32.370
- Yeah, that's a blessing.

10:32.414 --> 10:33.937
I mean, when I came
back from deployment

10:33.981 --> 10:35.635
it took me almost a year

10:35.678 --> 10:37.637
before I found
something productive.

10:37.680 --> 10:38.681
- Oh, come on, Pops,

10:38.725 --> 10:39.987
you know I got my
brother's back.

10:40.030 --> 10:40.901
You know I ain't gonna
let you come home

10:40.944 --> 10:42.076
with nothing to do, man!

10:44.034 --> 10:46.515
- I'm happy for you guys,
I'm happy for all of you.

10:48.038 --> 10:50.562
You guys may just make something
of yourselves after all.

10:54.479 --> 10:55.829
- Wait a minute!

10:55.872 --> 10:58.658
Side bar, where's the cake?

10:58.701 --> 11:01.486
I can smell it, I
just can't see it.

11:01.530 --> 11:03.227
- It is right here.

11:03.271 --> 11:04.489
Come on and help yourself.

11:05.534 --> 11:07.623
- Look at God.

11:07.667 --> 11:08.798
Won't he do it?

11:08.842 --> 11:09.669
-  Yes he will!

11:14.456 --> 11:15.675
- What do you think they see

11:17.154 --> 11:19.069
when they see us patrolling
their neighborhood?

11:19.113 --> 11:20.331
- Well, when they see me,

11:20.375 --> 11:22.899
they see a ruggedly
handsome man of the law.

11:22.943 --> 11:25.554
- Nah, that's not what I mean.

11:25.597 --> 11:27.643
- I'm just messing with
ya, I know what you mean.

11:27.687 --> 11:29.210
You're talking about perception.

11:29.253 --> 11:30.646
- Yeah.

11:30.690 --> 11:33.736
- Well, we're two
white police officers

11:33.780 --> 11:36.217
patrolling a predominantly
black neighborhood.

11:36.260 --> 11:37.827
Neither of us actually
lives in this neighborhood,

11:37.871 --> 11:39.481
you live a bit closer than I do,

11:39.524 --> 11:41.309
but neither of us
actually lives here.

11:41.352 --> 11:43.703
We don't have any friends, we
don't have any family here,

11:43.746 --> 11:46.618
but yet we're here,
every single day.

11:46.662 --> 11:48.838
How do you think
we're perceived?

11:48.882 --> 11:49.491
Watch you.

11:50.884 --> 11:54.191
- Hopefully we're perceived
as the good guys, right?

11:54.235 --> 11:55.932
- Hopefully as the
good guys, huh?

11:55.976 --> 11:56.672
Why the good guys?

11:57.891 --> 11:59.936
- I mean, come on.

11:59.980 --> 12:02.504
We're cops, good guys.

12:02.547 --> 12:04.506
- Are you one of the
good guys, Officer Tyler?

12:05.812 --> 12:07.204
See that, you hesitated.

12:07.248 --> 12:08.597
Never hesitate,
you have to know.

12:09.859 --> 12:11.295
Are you one of the
good guys, yes or no?

12:11.339 --> 12:12.253
- Yes.

12:12.296 --> 12:13.907
Yes, I'm one of the good guys.

12:13.950 --> 12:16.823
- Listen, stop worrying
about perceptions.

12:16.866 --> 12:18.738
If you let the streets
dictate who you are,

12:18.781 --> 12:20.391
you'd be torn to
shreds out here.

12:20.435 --> 12:22.524
You need to know who
you are from the get go.

12:22.567 --> 12:24.787
Focus on staying one
of the good guys.

12:24.831 --> 12:26.397
And don't think just because
you're wearing that uniform

12:26.441 --> 12:28.573
you're automatically
one of the good guys.

12:28.617 --> 12:30.967
If you were a scumbag
before you put that on,

12:31.011 --> 12:32.882
there's a good chance
you're still a scumbag.

12:32.926 --> 12:35.058
- Nah, I wasn't a scumbag
before, and I'm certainly

12:35.102 --> 12:36.103
not a scumbag now.

12:36.146 --> 12:38.061
You know what I think?

12:38.105 --> 12:40.063
How long have you
been on the force?

12:40.107 --> 12:41.282
- 20 years.

12:41.325 --> 12:42.283
I'm no spring chicken.

12:43.632 --> 12:45.329
- Yeah, well, it's
starting to show.

12:45.373 --> 12:46.983
- What do you mean by that?

12:54.904 --> 12:56.732
- Give us the money,
nobody gets hurt.

12:59.953 --> 13:01.476
Robbery in progress,

13:01.519 --> 13:02.956
5402 West Gellen.

13:02.999 --> 13:04.435
- 1108, in route.

13:20.147 --> 13:23.019
- Throw your weapon down
and get on your knees!

13:23.063 --> 13:24.934
Drop your weapon and
get on your knees!

13:36.206 --> 13:37.817
- Perp has entered
the Bend Building,

13:37.860 --> 13:41.037
following on foot,
14th Street North.

14:31.871 --> 14:34.786
This day can go
really badly for you,

14:34.830 --> 14:36.397
or we can leave here peacefully.

14:37.311 --> 14:38.051
Drop it!

14:45.754 --> 14:47.408
- Not bad, Officer.

14:47.451 --> 14:48.626
Not bad at all.

15:05.034 --> 15:05.905
- Hello?

15:05.948 --> 15:07.950
- Hey, I got some good news.

15:07.994 --> 15:09.604
-  Is it about the grant?

15:09.647 --> 15:10.910
- You know it.

15:10.953 --> 15:13.260
So, my dad, he
called in this favor

15:13.303 --> 15:14.914
from one of his friends,

15:14.957 --> 15:17.133
this super rich tech shark
he used to do business with

15:17.177 --> 15:18.743
a few years ago.

15:18.787 --> 15:21.442
He told him about what
we're trying to do,

15:21.485 --> 15:24.097
and he got us a meeting
with him on Monday.

15:24.140 --> 15:25.925
He wants to hear
about us, the kids,

15:25.968 --> 15:27.839
the after school
program, the whole deal.

15:27.883 --> 15:29.624
- Dude, are you for real?

15:29.667 --> 15:31.843
- Seriously, this is for real.

15:31.887 --> 15:33.933
It looks like Drew came
home at the perfect time.

15:33.976 --> 15:35.108
- Yo, he's gonna go bananas.

15:35.151 --> 15:37.023
This is perfect timing.

15:37.066 --> 15:38.981
Are we prepared for
a meeting, Chris?

15:39.025 --> 15:41.244
- If not, we better
get prepared.

15:41.288 --> 15:42.942
And keep in mind,
these rich guys,

15:42.985 --> 15:43.986
they need tax write offs.

15:44.030 --> 15:45.074
- Right, right.

15:45.118 --> 15:46.771
- We may be helping
out his business.

15:46.815 --> 15:48.077
We just have to tell
him what we've been

15:48.121 --> 15:49.861
trying to do these
past few years.

15:49.905 --> 15:50.906
We could do that, right?

15:50.950 --> 15:52.864
- We can definitely do that.

15:52.908 --> 15:54.257
Yo, we know this
thing inside out.

15:54.301 --> 15:55.824
- Exactly.

15:55.867 --> 15:57.913
This should be a piece of cake.

15:57.957 --> 16:00.002
So what are you
guys up to today?

16:00.046 --> 16:01.264
- Um, we're gonna head out.

16:01.308 --> 16:03.527
I'm taking Drew to
look for an apartment

16:03.571 --> 16:05.138
and a new car.

16:05.181 --> 16:07.053
- I guess he must be anxious
to get back out there.

16:07.096 --> 16:08.924
- Yeah man, it's like
he went in there a boy

16:08.968 --> 16:10.404
and he came out a man.

16:10.447 --> 16:11.666
He wants to get his own place,

16:11.709 --> 16:13.146
he wants to get a job,

16:13.189 --> 16:15.670
he wants to get a car, he wants
to hit the ground running.

16:15.713 --> 16:18.107
- I hear the military
will do that to you.

16:18.151 --> 16:21.110
Well listen, I'm only about
10 minutes away from you guys.

16:21.154 --> 16:23.634
I'll swing by,
I'll scoop you up,

16:23.678 --> 16:24.592
and we can ride together.

16:24.635 --> 16:25.985
- Sounds good.

16:26.028 --> 16:26.986
I'll let you tell
him the good news.

16:27.029 --> 16:28.596
I'll see you when you get here.

16:29.597 --> 16:31.164
Aight.

16:31.207 --> 16:33.253
- Six, seven, eight, nine.

16:57.886 --> 16:58.539
It's open.

17:00.062 --> 17:01.672
- You about ready?

17:01.716 --> 17:02.586
- I just have to
jump in the shower,

17:02.630 --> 17:03.544
it'll take me five minutes.

17:03.587 --> 17:04.371
- Cool.

17:04.414 --> 17:05.285
Yo, Chris is coming by.

17:05.328 --> 17:06.590
We're gonna ride with him,

17:06.634 --> 17:07.722
then we're gonna head
to the dealership first

17:07.765 --> 17:09.332
and then go grab a bite to eat.

17:09.376 --> 17:10.638
- Cool, sounds like a plan.

17:11.943 --> 17:12.944
I really appreciate you guys

17:12.988 --> 17:14.859
taking care of me like this.

17:14.903 --> 17:16.992
- Come on, bro, I
told you we got you.

17:17.036 --> 17:19.908
And you should probably
go get in the shower,

17:19.951 --> 17:20.996
you got this whole
room smelling like

17:21.040 --> 17:22.128
cheese and gym socks.

17:22.171 --> 17:23.172
You stink, bro!

17:23.216 --> 17:24.347
- Get out of here, man.

17:34.183 --> 17:35.967
- I'm just trying to
help you out, bruh.

17:36.011 --> 17:37.273
- Get out, get out!

17:45.934 --> 17:47.675
- There he is, the golden boy.

17:47.718 --> 17:49.024
- Oh, there he is!

17:54.682 --> 17:56.553
- Golden boy.

17:56.597 --> 17:57.380
- I know.

17:58.990 --> 18:01.167
- Thank you, thank
you, too kind.

18:02.429 --> 18:04.213
- You finally got a
taste of what it's like

18:04.257 --> 18:05.606
to be out on the street.

18:05.649 --> 18:09.218
- Yeah, it was pretty intense.

18:09.262 --> 18:11.002
I'm just glad I didn't flinch.

18:11.046 --> 18:12.308
- Flinch yet.

18:12.352 --> 18:14.136
It can get pretty
scary out there,

18:14.180 --> 18:16.834
but yesterday was
a good test though.

18:16.878 --> 18:19.489
- Listen, flinching is the
least of your worries, kid.

18:19.533 --> 18:20.751
Let me tell you something,

18:20.795 --> 18:23.145
I've seen grown
men poop themselves

18:23.189 --> 18:24.842
first week on the job.

18:24.886 --> 18:27.062
What you did out there,
that took courage,

18:27.106 --> 18:29.369
and don't let anybody tell
you anything different.

18:30.587 --> 18:31.893
- Okay, okay.

18:31.936 --> 18:33.242
This kid's head's
big enough already.

18:33.286 --> 18:35.331
Calm down with the platitudes.

18:35.375 --> 18:36.941
We gonna eat or we gonna
spend the rest of the day

18:36.985 --> 18:37.725
patting each other on the back?

18:37.768 --> 18:39.030
- We gon' eat.

18:39.074 --> 18:40.467
- Come on, man.

18:40.510 --> 18:42.033
He did good, give
the man his props.

18:42.077 --> 18:43.426
-  Thank you.

18:43.470 --> 18:44.993
- Don't fill his
head up too much.

18:45.036 --> 18:47.038
We got lucky out
there the other day.

18:47.082 --> 18:48.127
That guy decided to run,

18:48.170 --> 18:50.564
it doesn't always
play out like that.

18:50.607 --> 18:52.174
- No, it sure don't.

18:52.218 --> 18:54.829
A good day can turn into a
nightmare at the drop of a hat.

18:54.872 --> 18:56.222
- Why you trying
to scare the guy?

18:56.265 --> 18:57.397
- Hey, I'm just
trying to give the kid

18:57.440 --> 18:59.181
an honest point of view.

18:59.225 --> 19:02.184
Hope for the best, but always
be prepared for the worst.

19:02.228 --> 19:02.967
Always.

19:03.011 --> 19:03.664
-  Absolutely.

19:09.060 --> 19:11.672
- You know it bro, you know it.

19:13.500 --> 19:15.676
- Tracy just texted me, I
told her to meet us here

19:15.719 --> 19:17.460
because our boy Chris
has some important news

19:17.504 --> 19:19.549
to share with the group.
- You got some good news?

19:19.593 --> 19:20.681
- Yup, I do.

19:20.724 --> 19:21.856
But we gotta wait for Tracy,

19:21.899 --> 19:23.118
because it concerns her too.

19:23.162 --> 19:24.511
- Is it that important?

19:24.554 --> 19:26.121
- Yup, it's that important.

19:26.165 --> 19:28.906
- Hey, I don't know about
ya'll, but I am hungry, man.

19:28.950 --> 19:30.125
- Man, your default is hunger.

19:30.169 --> 19:31.431
-  Whatever.

19:31.474 --> 19:33.041
- I don't think I
know another person

19:33.084 --> 19:34.477
who eats as much as you!
- Yes you do, our dad, man,

19:34.521 --> 19:36.000
he eats like an elephant, bro.

19:37.001 --> 19:38.525
Hey, Grace, what's up?

19:38.568 --> 19:39.439
- Hey, Grace!

19:39.482 --> 19:40.440
- Drew!

19:40.483 --> 19:41.789
Welcome back.

19:41.832 --> 19:43.138
When did you get in?

19:43.182 --> 19:43.878
-  I just
got in yesterday.

19:43.921 --> 19:45.358
So good to see you!

19:45.401 --> 19:46.794
-  How come you guys
didn't tell me he was here?

19:46.837 --> 19:48.274
- No, don't look at me, don't.

19:48.317 --> 19:49.318
- Anyway...

19:49.362 --> 19:51.190
It's
good to see you too.

19:51.233 --> 19:53.801
- So, what you been up
to while I was gone?

19:53.844 --> 19:58.109
- Finishing up high school,
applying and touring colleges,

19:58.153 --> 20:00.024
that's pretty much been my life.

20:00.068 --> 20:03.071
I guess it paid off though,
I got accepted into USF,

20:03.114 --> 20:04.333
the music and art program.

20:04.377 --> 20:06.335
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations, Grace.

20:06.379 --> 20:07.249
- That's great news.
- Way to go, girl.

20:07.293 --> 20:08.163
- Thank you.

20:08.207 --> 20:09.208
I really couldn't have done it

20:09.251 --> 20:10.905
without you guys and Tracy.

20:10.948 --> 20:12.602
The after school program
helped to keep me focused

20:12.646 --> 20:13.908
and out of trouble.

20:13.951 --> 20:15.214
- Grace, you were
already awesome.

20:15.257 --> 20:16.127
Now, we may have
helped you channel

20:16.171 --> 20:17.955
all of that energy and effort,

20:17.999 --> 20:20.001
but as far as the
elements of greatness,

20:20.044 --> 20:21.132
it was already there.

20:21.176 --> 20:22.308
- Well, thanks to you.

20:22.351 --> 20:23.700
-  You are welcome.

20:23.744 --> 20:25.006
- Now let me get your guys'
order before my other job.

20:25.049 --> 20:26.703
What can
I get for you, Chris?

20:26.747 --> 20:28.314
-  Can I get a
Coke with lots of ice?

20:28.357 --> 20:30.054
- I want a vanilla
shake, please.

20:31.360 --> 20:32.840
- Just a glass of
water for me, thanks.

20:32.883 --> 20:34.320
- Okay, all right.

20:34.363 --> 20:36.409
I'll get those out to
you in just a second.

20:36.452 --> 20:38.628
Give you a couple of minutes
to look over the menus.

20:38.672 --> 20:39.847
-  Thanks, Grace.

20:39.890 --> 20:41.065
- Good seeing you too.

20:41.109 --> 20:43.198
- Good seeing you,
Grace, good seeing you.

20:43.242 --> 20:43.981
- Isn't she awesome?

20:44.025 --> 20:44.808
- That was pretty cool.

20:44.852 --> 20:46.462
- Yeah, bro, it was.

20:46.506 --> 20:48.334
- Hey, I gotta ask you.

20:48.377 --> 20:49.857
Who were those two older
gentlemen at your party?

20:49.900 --> 20:52.294
I thought I knew everybody.

20:52.338 --> 20:54.035
- The man with the one
leg was Tim Mitchell,

20:54.078 --> 20:56.124
and the other gentleman
was Hector Diaz.

20:56.167 --> 20:57.734
They served with our
dad in the Gulf War.

20:57.778 --> 20:58.692
Tim lost his leg there,

20:58.735 --> 21:00.302
they're all in the same unit.

21:00.346 --> 21:01.738
- How'd he lose it?

21:01.782 --> 21:03.305
- RPG.

21:03.349 --> 21:04.480
The unit was pinned down
in what they thought

21:04.524 --> 21:06.221
was a safe zone,

21:06.265 --> 21:07.962
in the middle of a firefight
with a group of insurgents.

21:08.005 --> 21:09.311
About a half an hour goes by

21:09.355 --> 21:10.530
and the firing slow
was just enough

21:10.573 --> 21:12.183
for them to take cover
in a nearby building.

21:12.227 --> 21:13.489
Turns out it was a trap.

21:13.533 --> 21:15.012
- Yeah.

21:15.056 --> 21:16.318
- RPG comes flying
through one of the windows

21:16.362 --> 21:17.580
and goes off just
yards away from Tim.

21:17.624 --> 21:18.625
Rips his leg right off.

21:18.668 --> 21:20.191
- Clean off.

21:20.235 --> 21:21.802
- Hector and our dad managed
to pull him to safety.

21:21.845 --> 21:24.457
They were all pretty
banged up but Tim,

21:24.500 --> 21:25.632
Tim caught the worst of it.

21:25.675 --> 21:26.981
- Mhm.

21:27.024 --> 21:27.764
- Really?

21:27.808 --> 21:28.591
- For real.

21:28.635 --> 21:29.375
- That is crazy.

21:29.418 --> 21:30.941
-  I know, bro.

21:30.985 --> 21:32.639
- Man, that sounds like right
out of "Black Hawk Down"

21:32.682 --> 21:34.902
or some "Saving Private
Ryan" kind of stuff.

21:34.945 --> 21:36.251
-  I know!

21:36.295 --> 21:37.644
- After hearing how
dangerous it was,

21:37.687 --> 21:39.254
you still wanted to enlist?

21:39.298 --> 21:40.647
- Well at first, not really.

21:40.690 --> 21:42.039
But after 9/11, I felt I had to.

21:42.083 --> 21:44.259
I had to do something.

21:44.303 --> 21:46.827
And a part of me wanted to
follow my dad's footsteps.

21:46.870 --> 21:48.132
- And what about you, Theo?

21:48.176 --> 21:49.438
How come you never enlisted?

21:49.482 --> 21:51.005
- Simple answer, bro.

21:51.048 --> 21:52.528
'Cause I don't want nobody
shooting at me, man.

21:53.355 --> 21:54.356
You already know, man.

21:54.400 --> 21:55.139
- I get that.

21:55.183 --> 21:56.489
- Hey Tracy, what's up?

21:56.532 --> 21:57.707
- What's up, Tracy?
- Come on in, come on in.

21:57.751 --> 21:59.405
Have a seat, have a seat.

21:59.448 --> 22:01.232
- Nothing yet, we just sat down.

22:01.276 --> 22:02.843
- Am I the only one who
doesn't know about this?

22:02.886 --> 22:05.149
- They haven't told me either.

22:05.193 --> 22:07.238
Okay, so, spit it out.

22:07.282 --> 22:09.328
- Yeah, come on, the
suspense is killing me.

22:10.851 --> 22:12.287
- You want to tell?

22:12.331 --> 22:14.245
- Nah bro, you gotta drop
that good news on them.

22:14.289 --> 22:15.725
- All right.

22:15.769 --> 22:17.597
So, I told my dad about the
after school program, right?

22:17.640 --> 22:21.035
So he tells one of his friends,

22:21.078 --> 22:23.298
and that friend loves
what we're doing.

22:23.342 --> 22:25.387
And that friend
also happens to be

22:25.431 --> 22:28.651
a multi-millionaire and wants
to meet with us on Monday.

22:31.306 --> 22:32.481
- Are you for real?

22:32.525 --> 22:33.395
- This is amazing.
- Yes, bro!

22:33.439 --> 22:35.049
- This could change everything.

22:35.092 --> 22:35.832
- Everything, man.

22:37.312 --> 22:38.400
- Come here.
- You gonna hug him?

22:38.444 --> 22:39.314
- Come here.
- Nah.

22:39.358 --> 22:40.446
- I'm gonna give you a hug.

22:40.489 --> 22:41.708
- No hug necessary, man!
- Hug him!

22:41.751 --> 22:42.622
-  This deserves a hug.

22:42.665 --> 22:44.232
-  I'm telling you!

22:48.367 --> 22:49.846
- And that's exactly why we need

22:49.890 --> 22:50.804
to get drugs off the street.

22:50.847 --> 22:52.153
- Yeah, you're right about it.

22:53.197 --> 22:54.547
- I'm just playing, but really,

22:54.590 --> 22:55.417
they look like they just won
the lottery or something.

22:55.461 --> 22:56.244
-  They do.

22:56.287 --> 22:56.853
- Yeah, yeah.

23:08.648 --> 23:10.301
- I'm nervous.

23:10.345 --> 23:11.825
I think I look nervous.

23:11.868 --> 23:12.521
Do I look nervous?

23:14.044 --> 23:15.524
- You're fine,
stop stressing it.

23:16.960 --> 23:19.398
- When I get
nervous, I get gassy.

23:21.356 --> 23:22.488
I think I'm gonna
use the restroom

23:22.531 --> 23:23.314
before the meeting.

23:23.358 --> 23:24.533
- Are you okay?

23:26.448 --> 23:29.320
- I'm just nervous, I
gotta go to the restroom.

23:29.364 --> 23:30.887
-  Christopher?

23:30.931 --> 23:32.323
Mr. Townsend will see you now.

23:32.367 --> 23:34.064
- Yes.

23:34.108 --> 23:35.588
- Are you okay?

23:35.631 --> 23:36.980
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

23:37.024 --> 23:38.373
Perfect, never better.

23:57.218 --> 23:58.393
- Please take a seat,

23:58.437 --> 24:00.090
Mr. Townsend will
be with you shortly.

24:00.134 --> 24:04.965
- Thank you.
- Thank you very much.

24:15.845 --> 24:17.281
- Everybody okay?

24:19.719 --> 24:21.155
Don't be nervous.

24:35.474 --> 24:37.127
- Pardon my tardiness.

24:37.171 --> 24:38.912
I had another meeting that
ran a little bit late.

24:38.955 --> 24:40.957
You must be Christopher,
nice to meet you.

24:41.001 --> 24:42.306
- It's nice to meet
you, Mr. Townsend.

24:42.350 --> 24:43.090
- Call me Eric.

24:43.133 --> 24:44.308
- I'm Tracy.

24:44.352 --> 24:45.309
- Nice to meet you, Tracy.

24:45.353 --> 24:46.920
- I'm Drew.

24:46.963 --> 24:48.748
- Strong handshake, I like that.

24:49.705 --> 24:50.619
- I'm Theo.

24:50.663 --> 24:51.315
- Theo.

24:53.013 --> 24:55.972
I can't help but notice that
you seem a bit perturbed.

24:56.016 --> 24:58.932
- No, I was just
expecting someone--

24:58.975 --> 24:59.889
- Someone older?

24:59.933 --> 25:01.587
- Yeah, yeah, somebody older.

25:01.630 --> 25:03.414
- It's okay, I take
that as a compliment,

25:03.458 --> 25:04.633
I get it a lot.

25:04.677 --> 25:06.330
So let's get down to business.

25:06.374 --> 25:08.768
I heard you all were working
on something pretty special.

25:08.811 --> 25:10.378
- Yes.

25:10.421 --> 25:11.814
We've put together this really
cool after school program

25:11.858 --> 25:14.643
for inner city kids,
kids in our community.

25:14.687 --> 25:16.819
Right now, we're focused
on music and art,

25:16.863 --> 25:17.951
and we're in desperate need

25:17.994 --> 25:20.301
of some new instruments
and supplies.

25:20.344 --> 25:22.216
We'd also like to purchase
a dedicated facility

25:22.259 --> 25:23.870
so we can broaden our efforts.

25:23.913 --> 25:25.654
That's where you come in.

25:25.698 --> 25:27.656
- I like what I'm hearing so
far. You got five minutes.

25:27.700 --> 25:29.528
Break it down to me as
if I was a five year old.

25:29.571 --> 25:32.661
- Our after school program
is called Clear Path.

25:32.705 --> 25:34.097
As Drew mentioned,
we're in desperate need

25:34.141 --> 25:36.578
of new instruments
in our own facility.

25:36.622 --> 25:38.145
Right now we're renting
space from the school

25:38.188 --> 25:39.625
that many of the
kids already attend,

25:39.668 --> 25:40.930
but what we'd like to do

25:40.974 --> 25:42.323
is create a fresh,
new environment

25:42.366 --> 25:43.933
for the kids we
already work with,

25:43.977 --> 25:45.500
and have something big
enough to accommodate

25:45.544 --> 25:46.414
even more kids.

25:47.589 --> 25:48.721
- How many kids do you have now,

25:48.764 --> 25:51.724
and how many have
completed so far?

25:51.767 --> 25:54.291
- Right now we have
about 60 kids enrolled,

25:54.335 --> 25:56.642
ranged from ages eight to 16.

25:56.685 --> 25:59.122
We've been in operation
for about six years,

25:59.166 --> 26:03.605
and in that six years, 485 kids
have graduated our program.

26:03.649 --> 26:05.955
- You average 80 kids a year

26:05.999 --> 26:07.653
with such a small team?

26:07.696 --> 26:09.698
- Yes, and I was deployed
for about a year,

26:09.742 --> 26:11.657
and so the team
was even smaller,

26:11.700 --> 26:13.659
and they still held it down.

26:13.702 --> 26:16.531
- Impressive to say the least.

26:16.575 --> 26:18.185
And you're a veteran, right?

26:18.228 --> 26:19.578
- Yes, sir.

26:19.621 --> 26:21.667
Two years in total with
one year of active duty.

26:21.710 --> 26:22.798
- You're like the poster boy

26:22.842 --> 26:25.453
for everything great
about this country.

26:25.496 --> 26:26.628
- Thank you, sir.

26:26.672 --> 26:28.587
But I don't want to
make this about me.

26:28.630 --> 26:29.979
This is about the
kids that we serve

26:30.023 --> 26:31.807
and how we can
hopefully work together

26:31.851 --> 26:33.069
to continue to serve them.

26:35.419 --> 26:36.420
- Wow.

26:36.464 --> 26:39.162
Honestly, you had me at hello.

26:39.206 --> 26:41.164
Chris, as soon as your
dad told me about this

26:41.208 --> 26:42.731
I wanted to be a part of it.

26:42.775 --> 26:44.951
A war veteran returning
home to serve his community.

26:44.994 --> 26:46.517
It's perfect.

26:46.561 --> 26:48.650
I do have one concern though.

26:49.564 --> 26:51.566
I don't know any of you.

26:51.610 --> 26:52.741
I don't know how
committed you are

26:52.785 --> 26:55.701
to the success of the
program or the kids.

26:55.744 --> 26:58.051
I hear what you're telling
me and it sounds great,

26:58.094 --> 27:00.575
but what connects
you all through this?

27:00.619 --> 27:03.317
Why should I trust you for
the next five to 10 years?

27:06.015 --> 27:11.020
- Eric, I've spent the
last six years of my life

27:11.064 --> 27:14.589
working in this
program with children.

27:14.633 --> 27:17.331
I didn't know a thing
about teaching kids.

27:17.374 --> 27:18.985
So I started taking classes

27:19.028 --> 27:21.901
on how to teach kids while
I was teaching the kids.

27:23.729 --> 27:27.471
We started this program
with just four instruments

27:27.515 --> 27:29.256
that were given to
us by our mother,

27:30.518 --> 27:32.389
who passed away a few years ago.

27:33.739 --> 27:36.524
I've personally invested
at least $10,000

27:36.567 --> 27:39.396
in new instruments,
art supplies,

27:39.440 --> 27:43.357
and the upkeep of the
facilities that we use.

27:43.400 --> 27:45.272
Tracy have written
letter after letter

27:45.315 --> 27:47.361
to every grant
issuing organization

27:47.404 --> 27:48.841
that you could think of.

27:48.884 --> 27:51.278
She's traveled the country
trying to find grant money

27:51.321 --> 27:53.976
or someone to invest
in our program,

27:54.020 --> 27:55.282
and she's doing all of this

27:55.325 --> 27:57.458
while teaching
five vocal classes,

27:57.501 --> 27:59.547
and pretty much running
day to day operations.

28:01.680 --> 28:03.551
Chris has been
here since day one.

28:05.118 --> 28:08.251
We taught our first
music class together.

28:08.295 --> 28:09.775
And he's structuring
the curriculum

28:09.818 --> 28:11.037
in the way that our classes

28:11.080 --> 28:13.692
are now official
college credits.

28:16.216 --> 28:19.698
But it was my brother
Drew who started it all.

28:19.741 --> 28:21.787
It was his idea to
offer our talents

28:21.830 --> 28:22.526
to the community.

28:24.703 --> 28:26.617
He was away for one
year on the battlefield,

28:26.661 --> 28:28.010
and while he was away,

28:28.054 --> 28:32.319
he was donating his entire
salary to this program.

28:32.362 --> 28:34.103
We're married to this.

28:34.147 --> 28:35.583
But we've gone as
far as we can go

28:35.626 --> 28:37.759
with our knowledge
and resources.

