on, let's do it.

41:46.242 --> 41:48.462
- You ever see this
much money in one place?

41:48.506 --> 41:49.768
- Never.

41:49.811 --> 41:51.944
With my salary, I'd
probably make this

41:51.987 --> 41:53.554
in 10 years though.

41:53.598 --> 41:54.947
If I don't get shot first.

41:54.990 --> 41:56.601
- Whoa, you better
watch your mouth.

41:56.644 --> 41:59.647
Don't even put that type of
negative energy out there.

41:59.691 --> 42:02.389
Life and death and the power
of the tongue, my friend.

42:02.432 --> 42:04.173
- You're in the wrong field.

42:04.217 --> 42:05.784
You should've been a preacher.

42:05.827 --> 42:07.133
- Nope.

42:07.176 --> 42:08.134
I'm right where
I'm supposed to be.

42:09.875 --> 42:12.399
- Hey, we got everything
bagged and tagged in there.

42:12.442 --> 42:14.009
You all covered out here?

42:14.053 --> 42:15.620
- We're almost done.

42:15.663 --> 42:17.535
- Dustin and Lamar should
be here any minute now

42:17.578 --> 42:20.363
to pick this all up and
bring it back to the station.

42:23.758 --> 42:24.890
- What's up, Tyler?

42:27.240 --> 42:28.502
You're thinking about
that big old mansion

42:28.546 --> 42:30.809
you can buy with all
this dirty money, huh?

42:30.852 --> 42:33.376
- Nah, not at all.

42:33.420 --> 42:34.595
I'm just glad we're getting
this off the street.

42:34.639 --> 42:37.119
I'm sure we ruined
some drug dealer's day.

42:37.163 --> 42:38.077
- I wish.

42:38.120 --> 42:39.513
The way they dashed out of here,

42:39.557 --> 42:41.167
this money wasn't
that important.

42:41.210 --> 42:44.518
Probably only took them a
few days to accumulate it.

42:44.562 --> 42:45.606
Domestic disturbance,

42:45.650 --> 42:47.347
648 Westbrook Street.

42:47.390 --> 42:48.653
- Copy.

42:48.696 --> 42:50.002
648 Westbrook Street.

42:50.045 --> 42:51.351
- We're gonna take this.

42:51.394 --> 42:52.657
- You guys be careful,
we're right behind ya.

43:08.107 --> 43:09.543
- See you inside.

43:09.587 --> 43:11.458
Yeah, I should be
home around five.

43:11.501 --> 43:12.502
Yeah, give me a call then there.

43:12.546 --> 43:13.547
Okay?

43:13.591 --> 43:14.243
Thanks, bye.

43:17.377 --> 43:18.465
Drew.

43:19.945 --> 43:21.207
Drew!

43:24.471 --> 43:25.428
Are you okay?

43:26.778 --> 43:27.561
- Yes, sir.

43:28.867 --> 43:30.651
I'm doing good, I was
just happy to be here.

43:33.567 --> 43:34.437
- Have you told anyone?

43:35.961 --> 43:36.788
- Told anyone what?

43:39.138 --> 43:41.488
- Son, you're not fooling me.

43:43.577 --> 43:45.492
I've seen that look
on your face before.

43:47.581 --> 43:48.756
You're having flashbacks.

43:50.279 --> 43:51.193
PTSD?

43:52.847 --> 43:54.544
Now have you told anyone?

43:56.329 --> 43:59.245
- It's nothing, and I
don't want to burden anyone

43:59.288 --> 44:00.942
with some bad memories.

44:02.030 --> 44:03.379
It'll go away.

44:03.423 --> 44:05.599
- No, no, Drew, that is
not the way it works.

44:07.035 --> 44:12.127
Listen, I've been retired,
in fact, over two decades,

44:12.171 --> 44:14.173
and I still have flashbacks.

44:15.696 --> 44:18.830
Yeah, I'm sitting
in my living room,

44:18.873 --> 44:20.266
beautiful day, and
all of a sudden

44:20.309 --> 44:21.528
some neighborhood kid lights off

44:21.571 --> 44:24.662
a pack of firecrackers and boom!

44:24.705 --> 44:27.708
I'm right back in the
heat of the war zone

44:27.752 --> 44:29.449
fighting for my life.

44:29.492 --> 44:30.363
Yelling, screaming.

44:32.104 --> 44:35.063
But in reality, I'm still
sitting in that chair

44:35.107 --> 44:35.803
in my living room.

44:37.631 --> 44:39.067
Man, it's so real.

44:40.765 --> 44:42.549
I can even smell the gunpowder.

44:45.639 --> 44:46.858
Now, now, you gotta
get some help.

44:46.901 --> 44:48.163
You gotta talk to someone.

44:49.599 --> 44:52.515
- I don't even know where
to begin to look for help.

44:52.559 --> 44:55.649
- I get it, 100%.

44:55.693 --> 44:57.869
When I first came
back, I was right

44:57.912 --> 44:59.131
where you are right now.

45:00.219 --> 45:01.699
I had the weight of the war

45:01.742 --> 45:02.830
sitting on my shoulders.

45:05.528 --> 45:07.705
Nobody had any answers, nobody.

45:10.577 --> 45:11.534
I was so lost.

45:14.189 --> 45:15.060
Lost my wife.

45:18.411 --> 45:19.717
Almost lost my children.

45:25.244 --> 45:27.550
It's more than one
person can bear.

45:29.465 --> 45:30.597
- What am I supposed to do?

45:31.598 --> 45:32.642
- I got your six.

45:34.340 --> 45:35.733
I'll walk you through it, okay?

45:38.997 --> 45:39.737
- Yes, sir.

45:57.929 --> 45:58.756
- Are you all right?

45:58.799 --> 46:00.496
- My dad hit my mom!

46:00.540 --> 46:01.454
- Secure the kid.

46:01.497 --> 46:02.585
Don't move until backup arrives.

46:07.547 --> 46:08.940
- Shots fired, shots fired!

46:08.983 --> 46:12.160
648 Westbrook Avenue, we
need backup immediately!

46:30.700 --> 46:32.572
- It's okay, it's all right.

46:33.878 --> 46:35.923
I'm gonna get you
out of here, okay?

46:35.967 --> 46:36.881
Who's here with you?

46:36.924 --> 46:38.186
-  Mommy and daddy.

46:38.230 --> 46:40.885
- Can you show me
where they are?

46:40.928 --> 46:42.190
Okay.

46:43.888 --> 46:45.193
- What do we have?

46:45.237 --> 46:46.804
- Two shots were fired before
Officer Eugene went in.

46:46.847 --> 46:47.761
- He went in alone?

46:47.805 --> 46:48.893
- Yeah, he went in solo.

46:48.936 --> 46:50.372
- Officer Brenda,
secure the back exit.

46:50.416 --> 46:51.243
And Tyler, stay with the kid,

46:51.286 --> 46:52.897
call EMT and backup.

48:47.925 --> 48:52.190
- Now, as far as private
investigator shows go,

48:52.233 --> 48:55.628
Magnum, P.I. was
by far the best.

48:55.671 --> 48:56.977
Ah, ah, ah!

48:57.021 --> 49:01.112
It had your action and
suspense, it had laughs,

49:01.155 --> 49:04.332
and the best part,
was that fantastic

49:04.376 --> 49:06.378
mustache he sported.

49:06.421 --> 49:10.643
- Now if you ask me, the
mustache was a little overrated.

49:10.686 --> 49:13.037
Yeah, kinda looked like
he had a caterpillar

49:13.080 --> 49:14.255
attached to his face.

49:15.691 --> 49:17.519
In actuality, Starsky & Hutch

49:17.563 --> 49:20.479
was a much better
show than Magnum, P.I.

49:20.522 --> 49:22.394
No, come on, no
really, seriously.

49:22.437 --> 49:25.875
Name me a duo that was better
than Starsky & Hutch, go head.

49:27.834 --> 49:28.922
Can't do it, huh?

49:30.315 --> 49:31.969
- Tubbs and
Crockett, Miami Vice.

49:32.012 --> 49:32.970
- Miami Vice?

49:33.013 --> 49:34.101
- Absolutely!

49:34.145 --> 49:35.146
- Oh, get out!

49:35.189 --> 49:37.365
- Miami Vice was
an iconic series.

49:37.409 --> 49:40.934
People tend to focus on the
flashy suits and flashy cars,

49:40.978 --> 49:44.111
but under that was a
serious crime drama.

49:44.155 --> 49:46.331
And a lot of what was
going on in the show

49:46.374 --> 49:49.464
was just a reflection of what
was happening in the city.

49:49.508 --> 49:51.118
- I couldn't see anything

49:51.162 --> 49:52.902
with the reflection off
those bright colored suits

49:52.946 --> 49:54.904
they wore with pastel shirts.

49:54.948 --> 49:56.558
Now come on, you tell me,

49:56.602 --> 50:01.085
what self respecting detective
is gonna wear pastel shirts?

50:01.128 --> 50:03.304
- Hey, ask the kid,
see what he thinks.

50:03.348 --> 50:05.132
- What would he know
about them old shows?

50:05.176 --> 50:07.134
- These kids love
80s pop culture.

50:07.178 --> 50:10.224
Son, tell him.

50:10.268 --> 50:14.446
Magnum, P.I., Starsky
& Hutch, Miami Vice.

50:14.489 --> 50:15.969
Which was the best?

50:16.013 --> 50:17.188
- What did I just walk into?

50:17.231 --> 50:18.885
- Boy, just answer the question.

50:20.539 --> 50:24.108
- Okay, Knight Rider,
that was my favorite.

50:25.065 --> 50:27.285
- The one with the talking car?

50:27.328 --> 50:30.984
- These kids don't know
anything about anything.

50:31.028 --> 50:32.768
Go stand over there
in the corner.

50:33.639 --> 50:35.162
Grown folks are talking.

50:35.206 --> 50:36.990
So where you boys headed today?

50:37.034 --> 50:38.078
- We headed to the
community center

50:38.122 --> 50:39.166
for a few hours, Pops.

50:39.210 --> 50:40.298
- Good.

50:40.341 --> 50:42.909
Kids will be happy
to see you back home.

50:42.952 --> 50:43.997
- Yeah, it's been a while.

50:44.041 --> 50:45.390
I'm looking forward
to seeing them.

50:47.783 --> 50:52.440
- So, you guys gonna tell me
what happened the other day?

50:52.484 --> 50:54.616
Your little run in
with the police?

50:54.660 --> 50:55.922
- It was nothing, Pops.

50:55.965 --> 50:57.445
Some things were said,
things got heated,

50:57.489 --> 50:59.099
you know, she let us
go with a warning.

51:01.362 --> 51:04.104
- You do realize
withholding the truth

51:04.148 --> 51:06.454
isn't much different
from lying, right?

51:06.498 --> 51:09.370
Okay, so, let's try this again.

51:10.371 --> 51:11.938
What happened the other day?

51:13.635 --> 51:15.028
- All right.

51:15.072 --> 51:16.812
I may have missed a
stop sign, you know,

51:16.856 --> 51:17.770
I don't think I did,

51:17.813 --> 51:19.685
but the officer pulled us over.

51:19.728 --> 51:20.947
She looks in the car at Tracy

51:20.990 --> 51:23.123
and just assumes
we're up to no good.

51:23.167 --> 51:25.734
She takes my license, she
goes back to her patrol car,

51:25.778 --> 51:27.127
and when she comes back,

51:27.171 --> 51:28.215
she tells me she wants
us to get out the car

51:28.259 --> 51:29.956
so she can search it.

51:29.999 --> 51:31.305
- Makes no sense, but go on.

51:31.349 --> 51:32.437
-  Yeah, it
didn't feel right,

51:32.480 --> 51:34.047
and I told the officer that.

51:34.091 --> 51:35.266
I told her that I felt
like I was being profiled

51:35.309 --> 51:36.745
and that she didn't
have a warrant,

51:36.789 --> 51:38.312
she couldn't search my car.

51:38.356 --> 51:40.053
- That probably didn't
go over very well.

51:40.097 --> 51:41.315
- It didn't.

51:41.359 --> 51:43.012
She said that if she wanted to,

51:43.056 --> 51:45.624
she could bust out my
windows, pull me out the car,

51:45.667 --> 51:47.234
and search it anyway.

51:47.278 --> 51:50.107
- Son, listen to me.

51:50.150 --> 51:53.762
I'm always gonna be on
your side no matter what,

51:53.806 --> 51:55.112
but you can't argue
with the person

51:55.155 --> 51:57.114
who has a badge and a gun.

51:57.157 --> 51:58.941
You're not gonna
win that argument.

52:00.204 --> 52:03.163
And for heaven's
sakes, keep your cool.

52:03.207 --> 52:05.165
You can't be out here
getting in a shouting match

52:05.209 --> 52:06.079
with law enforcement.

52:07.733 --> 52:11.128
Focus on not getting locked
up and getting home safe.

52:11.171 --> 52:11.998
- Yeah, but Pops
come on, she was--

52:12.041 --> 52:12.999
- "But Pops" nothing.

52:14.696 --> 52:18.178
Not getting locked up and
getting home safe, that's it.

52:24.271 --> 52:25.968
Theo told me your
meeting went well.

52:27.144 --> 52:28.145
Good.

52:29.363 --> 52:30.451
I'm proud of you two.

52:32.192 --> 52:32.975
Come here.

52:36.065 --> 52:37.545
You know, your get
your hardheadedness

52:37.589 --> 52:39.243
from your mother,
you know that, right?

52:39.286 --> 52:40.113
- Yeah, I know.

52:41.897 --> 52:42.768
- Are we done huggin'?

52:42.811 --> 52:44.161
We're gonna be late.

52:44.204 --> 52:45.423
- Yeah, we gotta head out.

52:46.685 --> 52:48.252
- All right, you
guys have a good day.

52:48.295 --> 52:50.210
- See you, Mr. Mitchell.

52:50.254 --> 52:51.211
See you, Mr. Hector.

52:51.255 --> 52:51.994
All right, Pops.

52:52.038 --> 52:52.691
- Be safe!

53:03.180 --> 53:04.006
- Oh, Drew!

53:05.094 --> 53:07.836
Oh my gosh, welcome back!

53:07.880 --> 53:09.751
- Thanks, it's good to be back.

53:09.795 --> 53:11.144
- So, when'd you get back?

53:11.188 --> 53:12.058
- I just got back
a few days ago.

53:12.101 --> 53:13.015
I've been taking some time out

53:13.059 --> 53:14.103
to hang out with the family.

53:14.147 --> 53:15.627
- Oh yeah, I definitely
feel you on that.

53:15.670 --> 53:17.977
I bet your dad's ecstatic
to have you back.

53:18.020 --> 53:19.326
- He is.

53:19.370 --> 53:20.197
They threw a party for
me, it was pretty cool.

53:20.240 --> 53:22.155
- Uh, where was my invite?

53:22.199 --> 53:25.027
- Hey, Dad did the
invites, it's not my fault.

53:25.071 --> 53:26.420
- Mhm, anyway.

53:26.464 --> 53:29.380
So, are you back for good
or is this like a visit?

53:29.423 --> 53:31.425
- No, I'm back. I just came
by today to say hi to everyone

53:31.469 --> 53:33.471
and give Theo a hand
with his classes.

53:33.514 --> 53:35.777
I'm gonna take a few more days
off before I jump back in.

53:35.821 --> 53:37.779
- Awesome. Okay, you
know you have to stop by

53:37.823 --> 53:39.128
and see Kimberly, okay?

53:39.172 --> 53:41.305
She's been asking for
you almost every day.

53:41.348 --> 53:43.132
-  Absolutely,
I've got a gift for her.

53:43.176 --> 53:44.699
- She's gonna be so excited.

53:44.743 --> 53:46.310
But anyway, holla at me
when you're done, okay?

53:46.353 --> 53:47.311
-  I will.

53:47.354 --> 53:48.312
- Aight.

53:48.355 --> 53:49.313
-  All right,
see you later.

53:49.356 --> 53:50.357
- Yes, see you later!

53:50.401 --> 53:51.271
- All right, Alex,
catch you later!

53:51.315 --> 53:52.185
-  See ya!

54:13.293 --> 54:14.816
- Drew!

54:14.860 --> 54:16.035
What's up, bro?

54:18.037 --> 54:19.908
-  Mr. Drew!

54:21.301 --> 54:23.216
- Are you gonna be
working here again?

54:23.260 --> 54:25.174
- Yes, I'm gonna be
coming back in a few days.

54:25.218 --> 54:26.088
- A few days?

54:26.132 --> 54:27.742
- Just a few days, I'll be back.

54:27.786 --> 54:30.397
- Let the man breathe,
he just got back.

54:30.441 --> 54:32.356
- Yes, stop crowding the man.

54:32.399 --> 54:34.401
You guys go back to your seats.

54:34.445 --> 54:37.056
These kids have been
asking and asking for you.

54:37.099 --> 54:39.014
- I've been asking
about them too.

54:39.058 --> 54:40.102
How's your class going?

54:40.146 --> 54:42.017
- Art supplies are still low,

54:42.061 --> 54:44.019
but apart from
that, all is well.

54:44.063 --> 54:45.325
It's good to see you, Drew.

54:45.369 --> 54:46.805
- Thank you.

54:46.848 --> 54:47.545
I'm gonna go holla at
Christopher's class real quick.

54:47.588 --> 54:49.111
- Okay, see you later.

54:49.155 --> 54:51.113
- See you later, Candice.

54:52.637 --> 54:53.638
- I know, right.

54:53.681 --> 54:54.508
- Hey!

54:54.552 --> 54:55.204
- Hey!

54:57.250 --> 54:59.731
- Give me my hug,
give me my hug.

54:59.774 --> 55:01.036
- What are you doing here?

55:01.080 --> 55:01.863
I thought you were gonna
wait a few more days

55:01.907 --> 55:03.082
before you came back in.

55:03.125 --> 55:04.562
- Well actually,
that's kinda my fault.

55:04.605 --> 55:06.259
I begged him to
come in and help out

55:06.303 --> 55:07.304
with my class today.

55:07.347 --> 55:08.957
- Oh, what are you
teaching today?

55:09.001 --> 55:10.916
- I'm gonna be doing some Ray
Charles and Rock Mendenhall.

55:10.959 --> 55:12.657
A little blues and classical
mixed in one class.

55:12.700 --> 55:15.224
- Okay, sounds like it's
gonna be an interesting day.

55:15.268 --> 55:16.704
-  You know it.

55:16.748 --> 55:18.097
- That's why he dragged me in.
- Ah, whatever, man!

55:18.140 --> 55:19.925
- Make sure you stop by
and say hi to Kimberly

55:19.968 --> 55:21.187
before you leave, okay?

55:21.230 --> 55:21.883
-  Okay, I'll
do it right now.

55:21.927 --> 55:23.232
- What's up, Chris?

55:23.276 --> 55:24.669
- I thought I heard
ya'll in the building.

55:24.712 --> 55:25.713
Aw, man!

55:25.757 --> 55:27.324
- Don't leave your man hanging.

55:27.367 --> 55:28.368
Good to see you, bro.

55:28.412 --> 55:29.717
- What's going on?

55:29.761 --> 55:31.023
- Just stopping by to
say hello to everyone

55:31.066 --> 55:32.633
and give Theo a
hand with his class.

55:32.677 --> 55:33.547
Have you heard
anything from Eric

55:33.591 --> 55:34.896
about the grant yet?

55:34.940 --> 55:36.811
- No, nothing yet.

55:36.855 --> 55:38.335
I hope we hear
something quick though.

55:38.378 --> 55:39.597
- Yeah.

55:39.640 --> 55:40.902
We had to cancel
the percussion class

55:40.946 --> 55:42.861
because the drums were
so old and beat up,

55:42.904 --> 55:44.471
they didn't even
sound right anymore.

55:44.515 --> 55:45.254
- Listen, guys.

55:45.298 --> 55:46.430
It's gonna happen.

55:46.473 --> 55:47.605
The grant is gonna come through,

55:47.648 --> 55:49.171
and everything is
gonna work itself out,

55:49.215 --> 55:51.913
I just hope it's sooner
rather than later.

55:51.957 --> 55:53.306
- Yeah.

55:53.350 --> 55:54.263
- Mr. Drew!

55:55.613 --> 55:57.789
- It's so good to see you.
- Are you back for good?

55:57.832 --> 55:59.399
- Yes, I'm back for good.

55:59.443 --> 56:00.487
I got a gift for you.

56:00.531 --> 56:01.836
- Really?

56:01.880 --> 56:02.968
- This is for you.

56:03.011 --> 56:04.273
- What is it?

56:04.317 --> 56:05.449
- It's a surprise.

56:05.492 --> 56:06.537
And open it when you get home.

56:06.580 --> 56:08.321
- Thank you, Mr. Drew.

56:08.365 --> 56:10.062
Can I ask you
something, Mr. Drew?

56:11.368 --> 56:13.457
- You can ask me anything.

56:13.500 --> 56:15.197
- Some of the kids
have been saying

56:15.241 --> 56:16.416
that we won't be
able to come back

56:16.460 --> 56:18.462
to the after school
program anymore,

56:18.505 --> 56:20.464
that it's going to
be closing soon.

56:20.507 --> 56:21.160
Is that true?

56:24.424 --> 56:27.035
- We're not gonna
let that happen.

56:27.079 --> 56:28.385
We're not gonna close it,

56:28.428 --> 56:30.343
we're gonna find a way
to keep those doors open.

56:30.387 --> 56:31.213
- You promise?

56:33.694 --> 56:34.391
- Pinky promise.

56:35.827 --> 56:37.568
- Hello, Auto Brothers Repair.

56:37.611 --> 56:39.874
This is Daniel Thomas,
how may I be of service?

56:43.182 --> 56:46.228
Aside from being talented kids,

56:46.272 --> 56:48.492
they are a great asset
to this community.

56:50.929 --> 56:55.150
Ooh, they've been working at
the community center for years.

56:55.194 --> 56:58.240
Investing their time
and money into it.

56:58.284 --> 56:59.590
Absolutely.

56:59.633 --> 57:01.548
If you need more
information from me,

57:01.592 --> 57:03.245
please feel free to call.

57:05.596 --> 57:06.553
- Who was that?

57:06.597 --> 57:07.249
Everything okay?

57:08.512 --> 57:10.427
- People about the grant.

57:10.470 --> 57:12.298
Doing their due
diligence on the boys,

57:12.341 --> 57:14.692
I guess they put me down as
a reference or something.

57:16.389 --> 57:18.391
Tell you what,
those boys are gonna

57:18.435 --> 57:20.567
make something of themselves.

57:20.611 --> 57:21.525
- Are you surprised?

57:21.568 --> 57:23.440
You raised those boys well.

57:23.483 --> 57:27.182
- Not surprised, I'm
just happy to see that

57:27.226 --> 57:28.575
they found their purpose.

57:29.924 --> 57:31.796
You know, I wish their
mom was still with us.

57:33.493 --> 57:37.497
All that musical ability,
they get it from her.

57:39.412 --> 57:40.892
She'd be so proud of them.

57:40.935 --> 57:42.110
-  Yeah.

57:43.590 --> 57:46.898
- Breathing is very important
for good vocal expression.

57:46.941 --> 57:48.943
Controlling how you
release your breath

57:48.987 --> 57:51.729
can enhance the
delivery of each note.

57:51.772 --> 57:53.600
And, as you may have guessed,

57:53.644 --> 57:56.603
we will be focusing on
breathing next week.

