So here's an exercise I
want you guys to practice

57:58.736 --> 58:00.302
when you go home.

58:00.346 --> 58:04.742
You want to stand up so your
tummy is fully extended,

58:06.439 --> 58:08.572
and then you want to take
a deep breath and hold it

58:08.615 --> 58:10.791
before you release
your notes, like this.

58:12.271 --> 58:15.404
♪ La, la, la, la, la, la, la

58:19.626 --> 58:21.585
All right, that's all the
time we have for today,

58:21.628 --> 58:22.890
I'll see you guys next week.

58:22.934 --> 58:24.849
Practice your vocal exercises,

58:24.892 --> 58:27.460
and try not to stress
your vocal chords.

58:27.504 --> 58:28.505
Okay?

58:28.548 --> 58:29.506
- Okay.

58:29.549 --> 58:30.942
- All right, bye
guys, thank you.

58:36.425 --> 58:38.253
- Hey.

58:38.297 --> 58:39.167
We're gonna go grab some grub,

58:39.211 --> 58:40.081
you want to roll with us?

58:40.125 --> 58:41.430
- Sure, give me five minutes.

58:41.474 --> 58:42.214
- All right, cool,
meet us out front.

58:42.257 --> 58:42.910
-  Okay.

58:45.478 --> 58:47.001
- It was so easy.

58:47.045 --> 58:49.134
I just sort of fell into it.

58:50.439 --> 58:52.180
I would tell the doctor
that I had back pains,

58:52.224 --> 58:54.269
and he would write
me a prescription,

58:54.313 --> 58:55.444
no questions asked.

58:56.533 --> 58:58.926
This went on for
about three years,

58:58.970 --> 59:02.495
and I wasn't buying
drugs in some back alley.

59:02.539 --> 59:03.627
He didn't look
like what I thought

59:03.670 --> 59:05.542
a drug dealer looked like.

59:05.585 --> 59:08.545
He wore a lab coat and a tie,

59:08.588 --> 59:10.155
but he was my drug dealer,

59:10.198 --> 59:11.809
and I was his faithful customer.

59:13.462 --> 59:17.466
A functioning addict with
a husband and two children.

59:17.510 --> 59:20.208
I look back on that time
and it terrifies me.

59:21.514 --> 59:22.646
If it weren't for
the grace of God,

59:22.689 --> 59:25.736
I don't know where my
life would be right now.

59:25.779 --> 59:29.130
I'm thankful, thankful
that I'm here now

59:29.174 --> 59:30.392
and not there anymore.

59:35.963 --> 59:37.661
- Thank you for sharing
with us, Marilyn.

59:37.704 --> 59:41.099
And we're thankful to have
you here with us as well.

59:41.142 --> 59:41.795
Who's next?

59:42.970 --> 59:43.928
What about you, Christopher?

59:43.971 --> 59:45.582
Would you like to share with us?

59:47.409 --> 59:48.149
- Sure.

59:49.586 --> 59:51.892
Yeah, things are
going really good.

59:51.936 --> 59:54.808
I'm going on seven
years clean now,

59:54.852 --> 59:56.593
no pills or alcohol.

59:59.160 --> 1:00:00.335
Seven years.

1:00:02.076 --> 1:00:03.034
When I started this journey,

1:00:03.077 --> 1:00:05.427
I didn't think it was possible.

1:00:05.471 --> 1:00:07.473
I couldn't see anything
past the addiction.

1:00:09.518 --> 1:00:11.477
I'd been a slave to
pills for so long

1:00:11.520 --> 1:00:13.566
that I'd forgotten what
it was like to be free.

1:00:16.569 --> 1:00:18.353
You all have
inspired me so much.

1:00:19.920 --> 1:00:22.401
And ya'll believed in me
when I didn't believe in me.

1:00:24.403 --> 1:00:27.536
Marilyn, I vividly remember
you calling to check on me,

1:00:27.580 --> 1:00:29.016
May 10th, 2012.

1:00:31.018 --> 1:00:32.585
I almost relapsed that day.

1:00:34.892 --> 1:00:36.589
And you called to say hello,

1:00:36.633 --> 1:00:38.591
stayed on the phone
with me for hours.

1:00:40.680 --> 1:00:42.551
That phone call
probably saved my life.

1:00:44.379 --> 1:00:46.077
- That's why having a
support system like this

1:00:46.120 --> 1:00:46.773
is so important.

1:00:48.601 --> 1:00:51.038
But you have to recognize
that you need help.

1:00:51.082 --> 1:00:52.649
And with that, comes change.

1:00:54.172 --> 1:00:55.739
What are some of the
changes that you had to make

1:00:55.782 --> 1:00:57.915
in order to be where
you are right now today?

1:00:59.351 --> 1:01:01.222
- Aside from connecting
with this group,

1:01:02.659 --> 1:01:04.748
I would say a change
in my environment

1:01:04.791 --> 1:01:05.705
and keeping my hands busy.

1:01:07.794 --> 1:01:08.969
I had to get out of
my old neighborhood

1:01:09.013 --> 1:01:10.362
and my old way of thinking.

1:01:12.233 --> 1:01:13.757
I lost a few friends
along the way,

1:01:13.800 --> 1:01:16.498
but I gained some new ones.

1:01:16.542 --> 1:01:17.674
- Tell us about your new friends

1:01:17.717 --> 1:01:19.763
and your new environment.

1:01:19.806 --> 1:01:21.547
- My new friends?

1:01:21.590 --> 1:01:23.462
Fellow musicians that
help me stay focused

1:01:23.505 --> 1:01:24.768
on what's really important,

1:01:26.465 --> 1:01:27.640
and my new environment is
this after school program

1:01:27.684 --> 1:01:29.729
for inner city kids.

1:01:29.773 --> 1:01:31.688
I teach bass and drums.

1:01:31.731 --> 1:01:34.603
I've been doing that for
about five, six years.

1:01:34.647 --> 1:01:35.517
It's given me a purpose.

1:01:37.128 --> 1:01:40.087
I'm involved in something
that is way bigger than me.

1:01:40.131 --> 1:01:41.393
Something that
touches other's lives

1:01:41.436 --> 1:01:42.176
in a positive way.

1:01:43.787 --> 1:01:44.918
And I didn't have that before.

1:01:46.354 --> 1:01:47.268
It's valuable.

1:01:48.792 --> 1:01:50.794
It really helps me keep
things in perspective.

1:01:56.190 --> 1:01:57.278
Hey!

1:01:57.322 --> 1:01:58.627
What are ya'll doing here?

1:01:58.671 --> 1:02:00.151
- We're here to take
you to lunch, come on.

1:02:00.194 --> 1:02:01.718
You're paying, though!

1:02:01.761 --> 1:02:03.807
-  We'll bring
you back to your car.

1:02:03.850 --> 1:02:05.156
-  That's perfect.

1:02:05.199 --> 1:02:07.462
-  The door's open, bro!

1:02:07.506 --> 1:02:08.986
-  Cool.

1:02:09.029 --> 1:02:10.465
-  So how's it going,
man? How did everything go?

1:02:10.509 --> 1:02:12.119
-  What's up, what's up?

1:02:12.163 --> 1:02:13.077
- It's good.

1:02:13.120 --> 1:02:13.817
It went really good today.

1:02:15.383 --> 1:02:17.037
We were just sharing the
highs and lows of the journey.

1:02:17.081 --> 1:02:18.691
-  That's
good, that's good.

1:02:18.735 --> 1:02:20.475
- Talked a little bit about
the after school program.

1:02:20.519 --> 1:02:21.694
-  Oh yeah?

1:02:21.738 --> 1:02:22.956
- Talked a little bit
about ya'll as well.

1:02:23.000 --> 1:02:23.870
-  You talked about us?

1:02:23.914 --> 1:02:24.784
-  You talked about us?

1:02:24.828 --> 1:02:26.003
- What'd you tell about us, man?

1:02:26.046 --> 1:02:27.787
- Just told them a
little bit about Mindya.

1:02:29.876 --> 1:02:30.747
- Really?

1:02:30.790 --> 1:02:31.443
Mind ya business?

1:02:32.705 --> 1:02:34.315
Very funny.

1:02:34.359 --> 1:02:35.708
The guy came out of
there with jokes.

