and you're gonna like it too.

1:03:02.866 --> 1:03:03.997
- Boo!

1:03:04.041 --> 1:03:05.869
- A burger can't be a
burger without meat.

1:03:07.218 --> 1:03:08.567
- Let's start the car,
come on, I'm hungry.

1:03:08.610 --> 1:03:09.916
- All right, fine.

1:03:09.960 --> 1:03:11.004
All right, listen, I'm
just letting ya'll know,

1:03:11.048 --> 1:03:12.484
Drew ain't got no seat belts,

1:03:12.527 --> 1:03:13.877
so you better hold on tight.

1:03:13.920 --> 1:03:14.660
- Better hold on tight.
- Hold on, hold on, hold on.

1:03:14.703 --> 1:03:15.400
Ya'll ready?

1:03:15.443 --> 1:03:16.836
Hold on.

1:03:16.880 --> 1:03:18.925
- Wait, wait, wait, wait,
wait, wait, wait, wait,

1:03:18.969 --> 1:03:20.274
wait, wait, let it--

1:03:20.318 --> 1:03:21.319
- Yo!
- That just happened?

1:03:21.362 --> 1:03:22.711
- Hold on.

1:03:22.755 --> 1:03:24.017
You wanna talk to her,
you wanna talk to her?

1:03:24.061 --> 1:03:24.801
- Listen here, baby.

1:03:24.844 --> 1:03:26.193
I want you to start.

1:03:27.629 --> 1:03:29.457
Prove me right, prove me right.

1:03:29.501 --> 1:03:30.415
I believe in you.

1:03:30.458 --> 1:03:31.764
Go ahead, go ahead.

1:03:31.808 --> 1:03:32.809
-  All right,
hold on, hold on.

1:03:32.852 --> 1:03:34.419
- My baby, it's my
baby, watch this.

1:03:34.462 --> 1:03:35.812
- Oh!

1:03:37.117 --> 1:03:38.379
- Now talk about my
car, yeah, keep talking.

1:03:38.423 --> 1:03:39.424
- Yo, we out.

1:03:39.467 --> 1:03:40.817
Ayo, hold on ya'll.

1:03:40.860 --> 1:03:42.949
Lord help us please,
Lord help us please.

1:03:42.993 --> 1:03:43.732
Hold on, hold on.

1:03:43.776 --> 1:03:45.038
Let's do it.

1:03:45.082 --> 1:03:45.734
Woo!

1:03:54.613 --> 1:03:56.136
- Doesn't that look
like the vehicle

1:03:56.180 --> 1:03:57.572
that was reported stolen
from Highland Park

1:03:57.616 --> 1:03:58.269
a few weeks ago?

1:04:01.141 --> 1:04:02.795
- How do you
remember this stuff?

1:04:02.839 --> 1:04:04.318
- Being young has its benefits.

1:04:05.711 --> 1:04:06.799
- Wiseguy.

1:04:20.073 --> 1:04:21.814
- There's no tag on the car but,

1:04:21.858 --> 1:04:22.902
I'm sure this is the one.

1:04:22.946 --> 1:04:24.251
How do you want to do this?

1:04:26.253 --> 1:04:27.820
- All right.

1:04:27.864 --> 1:04:29.561
I'm gonna let you take
the lead on this one.

1:04:29.604 --> 1:04:30.997
Try not to alarm anyone.

1:04:31.041 --> 1:04:32.912
We just want to make
sure this is or isn't

1:04:32.956 --> 1:04:34.827
the vehicle that's
reported stolen.

1:04:34.871 --> 1:04:36.698
Let's secure the driver first,

1:04:36.742 --> 1:04:38.700
then get everyone else
out of the vehicle.

1:04:38.744 --> 1:04:40.964
Keep your eyes wide
open, and stay calm.

1:04:41.007 --> 1:04:41.878
Let's go.

1:04:53.933 --> 1:04:55.326
- Good evening, sir.

1:04:55.369 --> 1:04:57.154
Would you mind stepping
outside of the car?

1:04:58.764 --> 1:05:00.113
- Stepping outside of the
car for what, Officer?

1:05:00.157 --> 1:05:01.419
-  We just need
to speak with you.

1:05:01.462 --> 1:05:02.637
- Officer, we didn't
do anything wrong.

1:05:02.681 --> 1:05:03.856
We just finished
teaching a group of kids

1:05:03.900 --> 1:05:05.379
from our after school program.

1:05:05.423 --> 1:05:07.468
We're just trying to
get something to eat.

1:05:07.512 --> 1:05:09.775
- Just sit tight
for a second, ma'am.

1:05:09.818 --> 1:05:10.994
-  Just step
out of the car,

1:05:11.037 --> 1:05:12.952
and I'll tell you
everything you need to know.

1:05:12.996 --> 1:05:14.780
- Man, just do
what he says, man.

1:05:14.823 --> 1:05:16.216
Let's get this over with.

1:05:16.260 --> 1:05:16.913
- All right.

1:05:19.437 --> 1:05:21.874
- Can you all step out of
the car for me as well?

1:05:21.918 --> 1:05:23.920
I need you to sit up
over here on the curb.

1:05:27.967 --> 1:05:29.403
- Turn around for me sir,

1:05:29.447 --> 1:05:30.709
and put your hands
behind your back.

1:05:30.752 --> 1:05:32.363
- Why do I have to put
my hands behind my back?

1:05:32.406 --> 1:05:34.626
Can you tell me what's going on?

1:05:34.669 --> 1:05:35.844
I didn't do anything.

1:05:35.888 --> 1:05:36.976
- This is just a
safety precaution.

1:05:37.020 --> 1:05:38.064
If you did nothing,
then you have nothing

1:05:38.108 --> 1:05:39.457
to worry about, right?

1:05:39.500 --> 1:05:40.893
- Officer, can you please
tell us what's going on?

1:05:40.937 --> 1:05:43.156
We have rights, we know you
can't stop us for no reason.

1:05:43.200 --> 1:05:46.072
- Sir, just sit there and
be quiet for right now.

1:05:46.116 --> 1:05:47.378
- The quicker you turn around,

1:05:47.421 --> 1:05:49.467
the quicker we can get
you all out of here.

1:05:50.816 --> 1:05:51.599
- All right, man.

1:05:59.607 --> 1:06:01.000
-  Your car has no tags,

1:06:01.044 --> 1:06:03.263
and it fits the description
of a car that was stolen

1:06:03.307 --> 1:06:04.482
two weeks ago.

1:06:04.525 --> 1:06:05.744
- Whoa, whoa,
excuse me, Officer.

1:06:05.787 --> 1:06:07.180
My brother just
purchased this car,

1:06:07.224 --> 1:06:08.442
it's not stolen, man!

1:06:08.486 --> 1:06:09.139
Get off!

1:06:10.488 --> 1:06:11.837
-  Please,
you need to relax!

1:06:11.880 --> 1:06:13.360
- Whoa, listen, listen
to me, listen to me!

1:06:13.404 --> 1:06:14.535
-  Officer Tyler,

1:06:14.579 --> 1:06:15.580
do you have the
situation under control?

1:06:15.623 --> 1:06:16.885
- Listen to me, my brother,

1:06:16.929 --> 1:06:17.712
he didn't steal this
car, it's not stolen!

1:06:17.756 --> 1:06:18.539
Get off of me!

1:06:19.540 --> 1:06:20.846
- What is he doing, man?

1:06:20.889 --> 1:06:21.716
-  My brother
just purchased this car!

1:06:21.760 --> 1:06:23.196
- Man, we're not criminals,

1:06:23.240 --> 1:06:24.719
how's it cool to throw him
on the pavement like that?

1:06:24.763 --> 1:06:27.070
- I didn't ask for your opinion,
I asked you to sit there.

1:06:27.113 --> 1:06:28.027
You can sit there and be calm,

1:06:28.071 --> 1:06:29.681
or you could be arrested.

1:06:31.465 --> 1:06:32.858
- You're hurting me!

1:06:32.901 --> 1:06:34.207
-  You need
to remain calm.

1:06:34.251 --> 1:06:36.514
- Sir, get back on the curb!

1:07:11.940 --> 1:07:12.941
- Hello?

1:07:12.985 --> 1:07:13.986
Thomas residence.

1:07:17.076 --> 1:07:19.165
Yes, this is his father.

1:07:29.871 --> 1:07:32.178
The boys are gonna be
thrilled to hear this.

1:07:32.222 --> 1:07:34.137
- Yeah, I wish I had more time

1:07:34.180 --> 1:07:35.442
to give back to my community,

1:07:35.486 --> 1:07:36.878
but what I lack in time,

1:07:36.922 --> 1:07:39.403
I hope I can make
up for in donations.

1:07:39.446 --> 1:07:41.100
We're prepared to
offer a full renovation

1:07:41.144 --> 1:07:42.754
of the current facility,

1:07:42.797 --> 1:07:45.148
or the purchase of a new
facility, whichever works.

1:07:45.191 --> 1:07:48.151
Along with new
instruments, and of course,

1:07:48.194 --> 1:07:49.500
future financial support.

1:07:49.543 --> 1:07:51.154
But we need them in as
soon as they're available

1:07:51.197 --> 1:07:52.590
to finalize everything.

1:07:52.633 --> 1:07:54.853
- This is exciting news.

1:07:54.896 --> 1:07:56.985
The boys should be
home any minute now,

1:07:57.029 --> 1:07:58.726
and I'll have them
give you a call

1:07:58.770 --> 1:08:00.206
as soon as they get in.

1:08:00.250 --> 1:08:01.555
- Alrighty, sir. It was a
pleasure speaking with you.

1:08:01.599 --> 1:08:02.730
- And you as well.

1:08:06.038 --> 1:08:07.083
Yes!

1:08:50.082 --> 1:08:52.302
Drew, this is your dad.

1:08:53.825 --> 1:08:55.392
I've been trying
to reach you guys.

1:08:57.133 --> 1:08:59.570
Eric called, and he
wants to make a donation

1:08:59.613 --> 1:09:01.049
to the after school program.

1:09:02.660 --> 1:09:04.052
Call me right back.

1:09:57.367 --> 1:09:58.672
Tell me what happened?

1:09:58.716 --> 1:10:00.239
- Pops, we got
pulled over again.

1:10:00.283 --> 1:10:02.285
For some reason, they
thought our car was stolen.

1:10:02.328 --> 1:10:03.938
- Drew just bought that car!

1:10:03.982 --> 1:10:05.897
- I know, I know, Pops. But
they said it fit the description

1:10:05.940 --> 1:10:07.551
of another vehicle that
was stolen in the area

1:10:07.594 --> 1:10:09.161
that we was in.

1:10:09.205 --> 1:10:11.990
They asked us to get
out of the car, Pops,

1:10:12.033 --> 1:10:14.340
then another officer,
he started to cuff me,

1:10:14.384 --> 1:10:16.821
and that's when it all went bad.

1:10:16.864 --> 1:10:18.170
They shot Drew!

1:10:18.214 --> 1:10:20.128
They shot Drew, Pops!

1:10:20.172 --> 1:10:22.348
They shot Drew, Dad!

1:10:22.392 --> 1:10:23.436
They shot him.

1:10:24.350 --> 1:10:25.699
They shot him...

1:10:44.370 --> 1:10:47.591
- First thing I want you to
know is I'm on your side.

1:10:50.246 --> 1:10:51.682
I'm here to help.

1:10:53.814 --> 1:10:57.035
But to help you, I'm
gonna need the truth.

1:10:58.645 --> 1:11:00.299
Not someone else's
version of the truth,

1:11:00.343 --> 1:11:02.693
